The Nigeria Center for Disease Control has announced the confirmation of 241 new cases of COVID-19, bringing the total number of confirmed cases in the country to 10819. NCDC made the announcement through its Twitter handle on Tuesday night. The agency revealed that 15 deaths were recorded, bringing the total number of confirmed deaths to 314. 


SaharaReporters Media It said, “241 new cases of ‪#COVID19; Lagos-142, Oyo-15, FCT-13, Kano-12, Edo-11, Delta-10, Kaduna -9, Rivers-9, Borno-8, Jigawa-4, Gombe-3, Plateau-3, Osun-1 and 1 in Bauchi. “10819 cases of ‪#COVID19Nigeria, discharged: 3239, deaths: 314.”  241 new cases of #COVID19;Lagos-142Oyo-15FCT-13Kano-12Edo-11Delta-10Kaduna -9Rivers-9Borno-8Jigawa-4Gombe-3Plateau-3Osun-1Bauchi-110819 cases of #COVID19NigeriaDischarged: 3239Deaths: 314#TakeResponsibility pic.twitter.com/VIRaG5lGiN 